      <article>
        <h2>What is the purpose of a README file?</h2>
        <p>A README file explains what your project is about and how to use it. It is the first impression for anyone visiting your repository.</p>
        <a href="https://www.makeareadme.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Learn more about READMEs</a>
      </article>

      <article>
        <h2>What is the purpose of a wireframe?</h2>
        <p>A wireframe is a simple visual guide to plan the layout and structure of your web page or app before you start coding.</p>
        <a href="https://careerfoundry.com/en/blog/ux-design/what-is-a-wireframe/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Learn more about wireframes</a>
      </article>

      <article>
        <h2>What is a branch in Git?</h2>
        <p>A Git branch is a copy of your codebase where you can safely work on changes, features, or experiments without affecting the main project.</p>
        <a href="https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Branching-Branches-in-a-Nutshell" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Learn more about Git branches</a>
      </article>
